        <body>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd. Mr. I. Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>London</placeName>
                <date>22 June 5614</date>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">In due course I received your<lb/> favor of <date>16<hi rend="sup"
                        >th</hi></date> Ulto with an order on <persName>Mr
                    Joel<add>?</add></persName> for Â£1.12.<lb/> which has been paid &amp; is to your
                credit, but I cannot<lb/> admit it as amt. of the 4 copies that you state are<lb/>
                sold for you had no authority to sell there for less<lb/> than 9/ for me &amp; that
                was allowing you 20pct as the<lb/> price they were sent to you at 12/ The price they
                sell at<lb/> here. Whoever told you <persName>Mr. Abraham</persName> sold them @
                8/<lb/> must have told you a falsehood for that Gent<hi rend="sup">n</hi>.
                would<lb/> not sell them @ 8/ &amp; remit me 10/ for every one he sold<lb/> The copy
                sent you was as I wrote at the time for<lb/> the purpose of review, which was never
                done, as to<lb/> your advertising it that was for your own benefit<lb/> for you were
                to have 3/ out of the 12/. You say you have<lb/> lost by my business which I cannot
                understand, but to<lb/> prevent any further loss to you, please send back the<lb/>
                copies unsold &amp; an order for the balance due me &amp; thus<lb/> close a business
                which has been far from pleasant or<lb/> profitable to yours &amp;c</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">
                <persName role="author">EHLindo</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
